Decision:

Use Clean Architecture to structure the Flutter Task Manager application.
Use the BLoC pattern for state management.
Use sqflite to store tasks record locally.

Assumptions:
Users can create and fetch tasks with a title, description.
Users can delete tasks they no longer need.
The application will persist tasks locally using SQLite.
The application will use Flutter Bloc for managing the state of tasks and their interactions.
The application will have a clean and intuitive user interface.